events.file: res://Audio/test lines/1 OLLIE Dak.mp3

events.text: Dak!!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/2 DAK hey ollie whats up.mp3

events.text: Hey Ollie. What’s up?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/3 OLLIE im freaking out.mp3

events.text: I’m freaking out!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/4 DAK yeah i can see that.mp3

events.text: Yeah, I can see that. Do your breathing.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/5 OLLIE dont tell me to do my breathing.mp3

events.text: Don’t tell me to do my breathing, this is serious!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/6 DAK whats wrong.mp3

events.text: What’s wrong?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/7 OLLIE look around were trapped.mp3

events.text: Look around! We’re trapped in this underdeveloped blank tech doomspace!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/8 DAK doomspace.mp3

events.text: “Doomspace”?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/9 OLLIE yeah what else would you call it.mp3

events.question: Yeah, what else would ya call it?!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/10 DAK its just an alpha build.mp3

events.text: It’s just an alpha build, Ollie. The game isn’t even close to done yet.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/11 OLLIE then why do we exist.mp3

events.text: Then why do we exist? Why are we here?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/12 DAK to try stuff out.mp3

events.text: To just… you know, try stuff out. To chat and stuff

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/13 OLLIE but just to chat.mp3

events.text: B-but… Just to chat? Is that really the sole purpose of our existence?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/14 DAK the boys are trying to figure out.mp3

events.text: The boys are trying to figure out how dialogue options work. It’s important.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/15 OLLIE were just here to say some lines.mp3

events.text: We’re just here to say some lines? Ugh. Lame.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/16 DAK its a bit more complicated than that.mp3

events.text: It’s a bit more complicated than that. I could have said at least three other things.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/17 OLLIE so do you want me to say the same thing.mp3

events.text: So do you want me to… say the same thing when you talk with me again, so you can try the other dialogue options?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/18 DAK nah we also need to test.mp3

events.text: Nah. We also need to test you saying a different line repeatedly after this dialogue tree is done. So when I come up to you again, say something else.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/19 OLLIE okay okay fine.mp3

events.text: Okay, okay, fine.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/21 DAK this is the hardsell.mp3

events.text: This is The Hardsell, Ollie. Come on. Our homebase? Where we live?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/22 OLLIE this this is it.mp3

events.text: This? This is it?!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/23 DAK are you okay.mp3

events.text: Are you okay? Did you hit your head again?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/24 OLLIE yes but thats not the point.mp3

events.text: Yes, but that’s not the point. Look at this dump! There’s hardly anything here!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/25 DAK it could use some decorations.mp3

events.text: It could use some decorations, I admit. We should hit up Hobby Lobby or something.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/26 OLLIE theres a bigger problem.mp3

events.text: There’s a bigger problem. How are we supposed to go to the bathroom?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/27 DAK theres gotta be a functional toilet.mp3

events.text: There’s gotta be a functional toilet here somewhere. I’ll look around.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/28 OLLIE well hurry up.mp3

events.text: Well hurry up. I saw Ted’s latest blender model and it makes me wanna shit.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/30 DAK its called GODOT.mp3

events.text: It’s called GODOT. It’s an open-source engine.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/31 OLLIE yeah but why arent we using unity.mp3

events.text: Yeah, b-but why aren’t we using Unity? Or Unreal?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/32 DAK because they take a sizable portion.mp3

events.text: Because they take a sizable portion of your profits when the game is released.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/33 OLLIE ah yeah that sucks.mp3

events.text: Ah yeah, that sucks. You’re right.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/34 DAK GODOT is fine.mp3

events.text: GODOT is fine. It’s Python, or whatever. It’s fine.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/35 OLLIE there is something undeniably sexy.mp3

events.text: There is something undeniably sexy about using an open-source engine for your game.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/36 DAK we can be GODOT pioneers.mp3

events.text: We’re gonna be GODOT pioneers, dude. It’s gonna be a selling point of our game.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/37 OLLIE for nerds maybe.mp3

events.text: For nerds maybe. I doubt normies are gonna care that much. But you’re right. Open source is cool. It’s like… the principal of the matter, you know?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/38 DAK yeah the principal of uh.mp3

events.text: Yeah. The principal of… doing things yourself. Or something.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/39 OLLIE except GODOT has tons.mp3

events.text: Except GODOT has tons of people working together to develop it.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/40 DAK yeah but together separately.mp3

events.text: Yeah but… together, separately.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/41 OLLIE also together together sometimes.mp3

events.text: Also together together, sometimes.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/42 DAK decentralized.mp3

events.text: Decentralized. Is that the word?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/43 OLLIE yeah that sounds nice.mp3

events.text: Yeah that sounds nice. Decentralized.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/44 DAK decentralized sounds nice.mp3

events.text: Decentralized. Sounds nice.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/46 DAK its like a purgatory of some kind.mp3

events.text: It’s like a… purgatory of some kind.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/47 OLLIE so do we need to do something.mp3

events.text: So do we need to do something to get outta here? Like, learn an important lesson about ourselves and the world?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/48 DAK maybe.mp3

events.text: Maybe.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/49 OLLIE or maybe its just a matter of time.mp3

events.text: Or maybe it’s just a matter of time before we’re… released.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/50 DAK or maybe were here forever.mp3

events.text: Or maybe we’re here forever.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/51 OLLIE oh my god.mp3

events.text: Oh God!!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/52 DAK relax.mp3

events.text: Relax. If we are stuck here forever, freaking out about it isn’t gonna change anything.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/53 OLLIE oh god oh jeez.mp3

events.text: Oh God, oh jeez!! What are we gonna do?! They don’t even have Xbox!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/54 DAK they dont even have physics.mp3

events.text: They don’t even have physics yet.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/55 OLLIE no physics.mp3

events.text: No - NO PHYSICS?!!?

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/56 DAK yeah try to jump.mp3

events.text: Yeah. Try to jump.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/57 OLLIE i cant i cant jump.mp3

events.text: I-I can’t… uuuuugh… I can’t jump, Dak!!

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/58 DAK yep no physics.mp3

events.text: Yep. No physics.

events.file: res://Audio/test lines/59 OLLIE screams externally.mp3

events.text: AAAAaaaaah!!
